value.name: The Residence
value.overview: A brilliant, eccentric detective must solve a murder in the White House residence — where the staff and guests at a state dinner are all suspects.

value.name: RESIDENT EVIL: Infinite Darkness
value.original_name: バイオハザード: インフィニット ダークネス
value.overview: Years after the horrors of Raccoon City, Leon and Claire find themselves consumed by a dark conspiracy when a viral attack ravages the White House.

value.name: Sandringham: A Royal Residence with Nigel Havers
value.original_name: Sandringham: A Royal Residence with Nigel Havers
value.overview: Nigel Havers reveals the secrets of Sandringham House and its vast 20,000-acre estate.

value.name: Diary of a Surgical Resident: Madoka
value.original_name: まどか26歳、研修医やってます！
value.overview: Madoka Wakatsuki, a 26-year-old resident, strives to find happiness while navigating the challenges of being both a doctor and a woman in the medical field.

value.name: Hello Residents
value.overview: The family of Mr. (Asfoor), who works in one of the contracting companies (Hassan Abedin), suffers from poor living conditions in the house in which they live, and is trying to find a new apartment that accommodates all of them, and the director of the company in which Mr. (Asfoor) agrees to grant him a new apartment with him and his family in one of the buildings he built, provided that he bears legal responsibility for the architecture, especially after a problem occurred.

value.name: Maria Graham: Diary of a Residence in Chile
value.original_name: María Graham: Diario de mi residencia en Chile
value.overview: Historical drama adapted from the diary of the famous British travel-writer Maria Graham who arrived in Chile in 1822 just as the country was becoming independent from Spain. She is a woman coming to terms with her husband’s recent death: In her discovery of this breathtakingly beautiful country, its people and its customs, she learns to live again.

value.name: Resident Playbook
value.overview: This spin-off of Hospital Playlist showcases the intense but heartfelt lives of OB-GYN residents learning the ropes at Jongno Yulje Medical Center.

value.name: The Unusual Residents of District S
Résidences secondaires : tous les Français en rêvent !
value.original_name: Résidences secondaires : tous les Français en rêvent !

value.name: Resident: Story of 5 Interns
value.original_name: レジデント〜5人の研修医
value.overview: Patients are brought in one after the other. Being put in an environment where there is a race against time to save lives, all they can do is stand there doing nothing. Though they still have a lot to grow as a doctor and as individuals, will they be able to overcome adversity and one day be able to proudly identify themselves as being a doctor?

value.name: Residential District
value.overview: In the center of attention is a large and strong Maslov family, which is not as successful as it may seem at first glance. These are ordinary people living in an ordinary apartment building on one of the Moscow streets. They are the same as us – they solve their problems, joke, quarrel, love each other, prepare to meet a new day. They live.

value.name: Residential Complex
value.original_name: 隣の家族は青く見える
value.overview:
Story depicts the conflicts and growth of families who live at co-operative houses.

Nana Igarashi is 35-years-old and works as a diving instructor. She is married to Daiki who is 32-years-old and works at a toy company. They live in a small apartment, while saving up to buy a house. They enjoy their life. Nana and Daiki decide to buy a co-operative house. They also try to have a baby. Nana and Daiki realize it isn't easy to have baby.

value.name: Kensington Palace: Behind Closed Doors
value.overview: An intimate look at the palace that has been a private home to the royal family for more than 300 years.
